message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Latvia, you have a few options depending on your personal preferences:

1. Walking: If you enjoy walking and the weather is good, walking to the grocery store is a great option. It will take you around 10-15 minutes to cover the distance.

2. Cycling: Latvia has a good network of cycle paths. If you have a bicycle, you can ride to the grocery store, which will likely take you about 5-7 minutes.

3. Public Transportation: Check if there are any bus or tram stops near your location. If available, you can take a short bus or tram ride to the grocery store. Check the schedule and routes in advance.

4. Driving: If you have access to a car and prefer to drive, you can easily reach the grocery store within a few minutes. Utilize GPS or online maps for the best route.

Consider choosing the mode of transportation that suits your needs and local conditions, such as weather, traffic, and personal preferences.
